          <msContents>
            <summary>[p]De venenatis affectibus et eorum curatione. (38 ll.) [/p]
[p]De febre quartana. (20 ll.) [/p]
[p]The beginning of the work on Fever is inscribed 'De febre quartana annotata pulcherrima / Que ego Johannes franciscus Collus [sic] Murrensis D. Luce filius sub excellentissimo Domino Francisco Frigimelica diligentissime scripsi'. [/p]
[p]There is a contemporary foliation 39-90, and this volume formed part of an original larger volume, which began with notes of the 'Discursus et consilia' by J. B. Montanus (MS.567) though this is written by a different hand. The vellum cover is also taken from the same 'Rotulus', mentioned above.[/p]
[p]Produced in Padua. [/p]</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="" source="IANA">Latin</textLang>
